Hi @Steven2006t, welcome to the forum! I took the liberty of putting the log in a spoiler to make scrolling the page easier for others, and I put your post in Tech Support. If you have mods installed, please let me know and I'll move it again to the proper section :). Hope you get a nice solution to your problem!

Being a Steam KSP customer myself, I don't actually launch ksp.exe or ksp_64.exe from Steam itself. Try browsing to C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Kerbal Space Program and launch ksp.exe directly. This should remove some of the Steam DLLs from the process, simplifying things.

You're using Build 15063 (Windows 10 "Creator's Update," release 1703) according to the OS DLL versions, which is the same build I use now. That alone isn't the cause.

I also have an NVidia card, so that alone isn't the cause.

I don't see RivaTuner Statistics Server or MSI Afterburner in there, but that's been the most common cause of KSP-related crashes on this Windows 10 build so, if you do use that, either stop that from running or update it to version 7.0 or later of RivaTuner Server. NVidia Share from GeForce Experience is better as saving game footage anyway.

Just to rule out a DirectX 9 problem from something hooking into that, see if you can make a shortcut to ksp.exe and add the command-line option "-force_d3d11" at the end. Or "-force_opengl" if that didn't work.
